    "markdown": "---\nformat:\n  html:\n    css: styles.css\n    embed-resources: TRUE\n    code-fold: true\n    page-layout: full\n    fig_caption: yes\n---\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n::: narrow-section\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"grid-container\" style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); justify-items: center;\">\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">848</div>\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">528</div>\n<div style=\"display: block; &#10;              color: #ff6400; &#10;              font-size: 1.25em; &#10;              font-family: Graphik; &#10;              font-weight: bold; &#10;              text-align: center;\">NA</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Currently Eligible for<br>Parole but in Prison</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Eligible for Parole in<br>the next 1-5 years</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">\n<span class=\"tippy html-widget html-fill-item-overflow-hidden html-fill-item\" height=\"338px\" id=\"htmlwidget-ceac71a4cc9b3087e162\" width=\"100%\"></span>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-ceac71a4cc9b3087e162\">{\"x\":{\"opts\":{\"placement\":\"bottom\",\"flip\":true,\"theme\":\"light\",\"content\":\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Not Available<\\/b>: .\"},\"text\":\"<span aria-label=\\\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Not Available<\\/b>: .\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" role=\\\"button\\\">Prison Sentencing<br>System&#9432;<\\/span>\"},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n\n<br>\n\n\n\n::: panel-tabset \n\n## Parole Eligibility\n\n<center>\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">How is Parole Release Eligibility Determined?</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">A prisoner serving a “time” sentence may not be paroled until they have served at least 1/4 of that sentence. In Montana, a sentencing judge who imposes a state prison term of more than one year may also impose the restriction that the offender is ineligible for parole and participation in the supervised release program while serving the term. Separate sentences must generally run consecutively. If an offender receives a consecutive sentence after incarceration but before a parole ruling is made on the initial sentence, parole eligibility is determined by aggregating the original sentence and the consecutive sentence. However, if the parole ruling on the initial sentence has already been made, the offender will not be eligible for parole on the consecutive sentence until after the offender discharges the original sentence unless a hearing panel orders otherwise. Due to the fact that an offender may still be eligible for parole on the first sentence, the hearing panel may allow the second term to commence for the purposes of calculating parole eligibility. Note, however, that this does not shorten the length of the consecutive sentence.</div>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">People who are Eligible for Parole</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"bar-chart\">\n<div id=\"htmlwidget-13ff56bbe0fd8fe4426f\" style=\"width:100%;height:454px;\" class=\"highchart html-widget \"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-13ff56bbe0fd8fe4426f\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\":{\"reflow\":true,\"width\":500,\"height\":350},\"title\":{\"text\":\"People who are Parole Eligible but Still in Prison by Race in 2020\"},\"yAxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":null},\"labels\":{\"enabled\":false}},\"credits\":{\"enabled\":false},\"exporting\":{\"enabled\":true},\"boost\":{\"enabled\":false},\"plotOptions\":{\"series\":{\"label\":{\"enabled\":false},\"turboThreshold\":0,\"animation\":false,\"cursor\":\"pointer\",\"borderWidth\":3,\"minPointLength\":4},\"treemap\":{\"layoutAlgorithm\":\"squarified\"},\"accessibility\":{\"enabled\":true,\"keyboardNavigation\":{\"enabled\":true},\"linkedDescription\":\"TBD\",\"landmarkVerbosity\":\"one\"},\"area\":{\"accessibility\":{\"description\":\"TBD\"}}},\"series\":[{\"group\":\"group\",\"data\":[{\"state\":\"Montana\",\"race\":\"White, non-Hispanic\",\"n\":606,\"prop\":0.7205707491082045,\"yearendpop_ped\":841,\"prop_label\":\"72%\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Montana - White, non-Hispanic<\\/b><br>72%<br>\",\"y\":72.05707491082045,\"color\":\"#FDE725\",\"name\":\"White, non-Hispanic\",\"colorv\":\"White, non-Hispanic\"},{\"state\":\"Montana\",\"race\":\"Other race(s), non-Hispanic\",\"n\":180,\"prop\":0.2140309155766944,\"yearendpop_ped\":841,\"prop_label\":\"21%\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Montana - Other race(s), non-Hispanic<\\/b><br>21%<br>\",\"y\":21.40309155766944,\"color\":\"#6AAD69\",\"name\":\"Other race(s), non-Hispanic\",\"colorv\":\"Other race(s), non-Hispanic\"},{\"state\":\"Montana\",\"race\":\"Black, non-Hispanic\",\"n\":32,\"prop\":0.03804994054696789,\"yearendpop_ped\":841,\"prop_label\":\"4%\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Montana - Black, non-Hispanic<\\/b><br>4%<br>\",\"y\":3.804994054696789,\"color\":\"#440154\",\"name\":\"Black, non-Hispanic\",\"colorv\":\"Black, non-Hispanic\"},{\"state\":\"Montana\",\"race\":\"Hispanic, any race\",\"n\":23,\"prop\":0.02734839476813317,\"yearendpop_ped\":841,\"prop_label\":\"3%\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Montana - Hispanic, any race<\\/b><br>3%<br>\",\"y\":2.734839476813317,\"color\":\"#2C6079\",\"name\":\"Hispanic, any race\",\"colorv\":\"Hispanic, any race\"}],\"type\":\"column\",\"dataLabels\":{\"enabled\":true,\"format\":\"{point.prop_label}\",\"style\":{\"fontSize\":\